South African Inflation-Linked Bond Yields Fall at Central-Bank Auction

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-08-26T09:27:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/south-african-inflation-linked-bond-yields-fall-at-central-bank-auction.html
Yields on South African inflation-
linked bonds retreated at a central-bank auction of 600 million
rand of the debt today.  The Pretoria-based Reserve Bank sold 215 million rand of
2.75 notes maturing in 2022 at an average yield of 2.26 percent
compared with 2.32 percent at the previous auction, the central
bank said in a statement on its Bloomberg page today. Thatâ€™s the
lowest yield since the debt was first issued in June 2010,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  It sold 20 million rand of 2.6 percent due 2028 at a yield
of 2.3 percent, and 365 million rand of 3.45 percent, 2033
securities yielding 2.28 percent, one basis point higher than
the lowest since May 2009, when it as at 2.27 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
